# Example Environment Variables for Netlify

# Copy these values to your Netlify site's Environment Variables section
# (Site Settings â†’ Environment Variables)

# Firebase Admin SDK Configuration
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx@your-project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYourPrivateKeyHere\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

# Gemini API Configuration  
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here

# Notes:
# 1. Replace the placeholder values with your actual credentials
# 2. For FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY, keep the quotes and include the full key with \n for newlines
# 3. Get these values from your Firebase project's Service Account JSON file
# 4. Never commit actual credentials to version control
